In [18]:
def scrape(url):
    url=url
    df = pd.read_html(url)[0]
    return df
In [19]:
df_pass = scrape(url = 'https://widgets.sports-reference.com/wg.fcgi?css=1&site=fb&url=%2Fen%2Fcomps%2F11%2Fpassing%2FSerie-A-Stats&div=div_stats_passing')
df_pass_type = scrape('https://widgets.sports-reference.com/wg.fcgi?css=1&site=fb&url=%2Fen%2Fcomps%2F11%2Fpassing_types%2FSerie-A-Stats&div=div_stats_passing_types')
df_shoot = scrape(url = 'https://widgets.sports-reference.com/wg.fcgi?css=1&site=fb&url=%2Fen%2Fcomps%2F11%2Fshooting%2FSerie-A-Stats&div=div_stats_shooting')
df_creat = scrape(url = 'https://widgets.sports-reference.com/wg.fcgi?css=1&site=fb&url=%2Fen%2Fcomps%2F11%2Fgca%2FSerie-A-Stats&div=div_stats_gca')
df_def = scrape(url = 'https://widgets.sports-reference.com/wg.fcgi?css=1&site=fb&url=%2Fen%2Fcomps%2F11%2Fdefense%2FSerie-A-Stats&div=div_stats_defense')
df_possess = scrape(url = 'https://widgets.sports-reference.com/wg.fcgi?css=1&site=fb&url=%2Fen%2Fcomps%2F11%2Fpossession%2FSerie-A-Stats&div=div_stats_possession')
df_misc = scrape(url = 'https://widgets.sports-reference.com/wg.fcgi?css=1&site=fb&url=%2Fen%2Fcomps%2F11%2Fmisc%2FSerie-A-Stats&div=div_stats_misc')
df_playingtime = scrape(url = 'https://widgets.sports-reference.com/wg.fcgi?css=1&site=fb&url=%2Fen%2Fcomps%2F11%2Fplayingtime%2FSerie-A-Stats&div=div_stats_playing_time')
In [20]:
list_df = [df_pass, df_pass_type,df_shoot, df_creat, df_def, df_possess, df_misc, df_playingtime]
In [101]:
#take only the second level (of the multiindex) for each dfs
for i in list_df:
    i.columns = i.columns.get_level_values(1)
In [28]:
for i in list_df:
    i.columns = ['_'.join(col) for col in i.columns.values]
    #print(i.columns.values)
In [29]:
df_tot = pd.concat([df_pass, df_pass_type,df_shoot, df_creat, df_def, df_possess, df_misc, df_playingtime], axis=1, keys='Player')
df_tot.columns = df_tot.columns.get_level_values(1) #ransf the columns with only the 2nd level_val of the multiindex df

fig = plt.figure(figsize = (8,8))
ax = fig.add_subplot(1,1,1) 
ax.set_xlabel('Principal Component 1', fontsize = 15)
ax.set_ylabel('Principal Component 2', fontsize = 15)
ax.set_title('2 component PCA', fontsize = 20)
targets = ['MF', 'DF,MF', 'MF,FW']
colors = ['r', 'g', 'b']
for target, color in zip(targets,colors):
    indicesToKeep = finalDf['Pos'] == target
    ax.scatter(finalDf.loc[indicesToKeep, 'principal component 1']
               , finalDf.loc[indicesToKeep, 'principal component 2']
               , c = color
               , s = 50)
ax.legend(targets)
ax.grid()

Label the PCs:¶

  • 1 PC (PC[0]): (negative) impact of 'Passes' or 'Passes Accuracy'
  • 2 PC: 'Shots & Creation' components
  • 3 PC: Type of Passes (High+Clearences+Progr Passes)--> 'def. minded passes'?
  • 4 PC: (negative impact of): Tackles, Int, Blcks vs (positive) Short&Med passes completed
  • 5 PC: Assist+KeyPass+Goal Creation
  • 6 PC: (negative) Vs Dribb%: % of tackle won vs Dribbles - (positi e) Aerials Won-Int (and xG!!)

Clustering¶

In [142]:
# var measure
wcss=[]
for i in range(1,10):
    kmeans_pca = KMeans(n_clusters=i, init='k-means++', random_state=11)
    kmeans_pca.fit(scores_pca)
    wcss.append(kmeans_pca.inertia_)
    
#'elbow' plot - WCSS    
plt.figure(figsize=(12,10))
plt.plot(range(1,10), wcss , marker ='o')
plt.title('WCSS - number of k')
plt.show()

Elbow plot suggests 3 numb of cluster. Other methods of eval, would be analyse the silhoutte plots

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

#create Player's name array
t = df_cc_k3['Player']
x = df_cc_k3['PC2'] # PC2
y= df_cc_k3['PC3'] # PC3

#cmap = sns.cubehelix_palette(dark=.3, light=.8, as_cmap=True)

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(18,20))
ax = sns.scatterplot(x='PC2', y='PC3', hue='Clusters', s=250, 
                palette='Set1', data=df_cc_k3)


for i,txt in enumerate(t):
    plt.annotate(txt, (x[i], y[i]), xycoords='data',
                ha='center', weight='bold')
    

plt.title('Midfielders Clustering', fontsize=18)

plt.ylabel("Defensive Minded (Passes)", fontsize=14)
